3198, "(fr)Overton Orbital, gunship Bravo 1 outbound to salvage depot."

3199, "(fr)Gunship Bravo 1, Overton STC confirms outbound trajectory."

3200, "(fr)Ross, all we've got are sensor ghosts. Whatever's out there's running silent. If you get closer you may be able to firm up the readings."

3201, "(fr)What am I looking for?"

3202, "(fr)I've transmitted the sensor data to you. You should see some flickering signals on your radar."

3203, "(fr)And Ross, be careful out there. We don't know what to expect."

3204, "(fr)Hold up Ross, got a fix on something. Check your hud."

3205, "(fr)Ross! Are you okay? We picked up a detonation in your area."

3206, "(fr)Yeah. Those signals you picked up? They're mines."

3207, "(fr)What? What are they doing here? This is a scrapyard."

3208, "(fr)See if you can find more. We can't leave any explosives floating around."

3209, "(fr)Ross, looks like you've found another one."

3210, "(fr)Careful Ross! Use your weapons to shoot the mines at distance."

3211, "(fr)All right! That's two down,"

3212, "(fr)Another mine detected."

3213, "(fr)We're still picking up a couple more signals out there."

3214, "(fr)Ross, what are you doing? You're supposed to be testing your gunship's weapons, not its damage tolerance."

3215, "(fr)Check your targeting , you've found another mine."

3216, "(fr)One more to go."

3217, "(fr)Got a mine near you."

3218, "(fr)Looks like you got them all. Good work Ross."

3219, "(fr)This doesn't make sense. No one's been through the area for weeks. Who set those mines?"

3220, "(fr)I'll head back to Overton. They better hike up our hazard pay, those mines were serious business."

3221, "(fr)One second Ross. There's faint sensor contacts from the far side of the field. You should check them out."

3222, "(fr)Lau, you're not going to believe this."

3223, "(fr)That's one of the station's salvage drones! And what the hell is that Stargazer doing?"

3224, "(fr)Looks like a bit of unauthorised salvage. These are probably the culprits Lau."

3225, "(fr)Gun ship Bravo one, this is station master Ferris. I want those interlopers apprehended. You won't get a single credit until it's done!"

3226, "(fr)That Stargazer is twenty seconds from spooling her impellers. Take out her astrogation ssytems before she jumps!"

3227, "(fr)Ok. She's not going anywhere. I'm calling in a security detachment to apprehend her."

3228, "(fr)What the hell are you doing? This is unacceptable! You've lost our best chance of finding out who did this."

3229, "(fr)I'm sorry Ferris. There wasn't anything else we could have done."

3230, "(fr)You promised me a competent pilot Lau! I'm never going to recover from these losses. You can consider your payment forfeit! Ferris out!"

3231, "(fr)Ugh, I'm sorry you had to go through that Ross. You might as well bring yourself back to Overton."

3232, "(fr)Your boss is a real bitch Lau."

3233, "(fr)Yeah. She is. I'll be glad when I'm out of this dump."

3234, "(fr)You didn't tell me this fighter moves like a sleepy hog Lau."

3235, "(fr)Don't be so rude. It's not a fighter, it's a missile gunship. It's not supposed to dogfight."

3236, "(fr)What made you decide to add missile pods? No one uses them nowadays, they're so easy to counter."

3237, "(fr)Missiles can still be useful out here in the fringe. There's a lot of obsolete old junkers out here, and not all of them use countermeasures."

3238, "(fr)Sorry, Lau. I didn't mean to be rude. I'm guessing the missile weapons systems are adding to the gunship's weight."

3239, "(fr)Of course they are. I tried to get the missile pods as light as they could, but it's a complex system. You need a lot of machinery."

3240, "(fr)It's a far cry from your shiny Commonwealth Ross. There's no gloss here. Everyone's doing what they can to survive."

3241, "(fr)Do you mind holding around the area for a while? Sulsian security tends to be...tardy and there's no one else around to help."

3242, "(fr)Depends. Do I get an overtime bonus?"

3243, "(fr)You're a funny guy Ross. Of course not."

3244, "(fr)Nice work. That'll wreck her jump calculations. Now take out her engines."

