3286, "Mission Title"

3287, "(fr)This is Ross. I'm clear and engaging manual flight control."

3288, "(fr)Look sharp lad, someone else's responded to the freighter's call."

3289, "(fr)Watch out. I see a cutter out there with at least five fighters."

3290, "(fr)Compass Rose, this is Katherine Lau on the corvette Hoshikuzu. We are here to render assistance."

3291, "(fr)I am Gadaria of the Malika People's Militia. My crew are assisting this freighter with repairs and have the situation under control."

3292, "(fr)This is Malikan space and you have no jurisdiction here. If you approach our vessel we will respond appropriately."

3293, "(fr)You have no claim over the Compass Rose and do not speak for her master. Put the freighter's master on the comms or there will be consequences."

3294, "(fr)Onyx corvette and fighters have gone weapons hot! Warming up PDCs."

3295, "(fr)Gadaria, we are an armed security vessel. We have authorisation to safeguard all outgoing merchant traffic."

3296, "(fr)This has trouble written all over it. Get ready for action, lad."

3297, "(fr)Oh I'm ready. I plan to be the worst thing that's happened to these pirate scum."

3298, "(fr)This Gadaria sounds like a proper tinfoil warlord."

3299, "(fr)There's plenty of the buggers out here all carving up their own little niche of space. No enforcers out here to keep them in line."

3300, "(fr)All right, that's enough warning. Warming up the PDCs. Kaur, spin the engines as fast as they'll go."

3301, "(fr)Hostile ships incoming. Ross, split and engage!"

3302, "(fr)Whiskey fighters down."

3303, "(fr)Victor wing taken care of."

3304, "(fr)All right you two, lend us a hand against the cutter's turrets."

3305, "(fr)Sulsian corvette, come no closer! This is your final warning."

3306, "(fr)That was good work lad. Looks like time in an Akrotiri tavern hasn't dulled your reflexes."

3307, "(fr)Hey, looks like being close to retirement age hasn't dulled yours either."

3308, "(fr)Compass Rose, this is Katherine Lau of the Hoshikuzu. Is your transceiver operational?"

3309, "(fr)This is Master Shafer. Our comms are intact. My crew was instructed by the militia ship not to respond to your comms through threat of violence."

3310, "(fr)Are there any casualties?"

3311, "(fr)Five of my crew suffered injuries in the initial engine failure. We've given first aid but there's no sick bay on board."

3312, "(fr)We can contact Azar to send a repair transport, but first I need to know what happened. "

3313, "(fr)It was that piece of junk impeller unit we got from Langchai. It blew the engine casing and tore a hole through the service tunnel."

3314, "(fr)We're going to need a realigned impeller unit. We don't have any spares on board or the expertise to install one."

3315, "(fr)Azar Station, we've got a stricken freighter in need of field repairs. Can you send a repair ship to our location?"

3316, "(fr)Message received, Hoshikuzu. The only auxiliary on site is the Hopewell. She's currently attending to salvage operations but should be available within three hours."

3317, "(fr)That's not good enough. Every pirate within a five system radius will have heard our distress call. We haven't got three hours."

3318, "(fr)That's the best you're getting Shafer."

3319, "(fr)Shafer! We're helpless out here. Get that frigate to take us on board, leave this ship to rot for all I care!"

3320, "(fr)You're out of your mind. We've a full hold of goods in here! Trinity Holdings will have my head if I lose this shipment."

3321, "(fr)That's all you care about. Money! Five of your crew are hurt because you cheaped out on a new engine!"

3322, "(fr)Sulsian ship! If you're listening, we've got injured on board. We can't wait out here for hours! Get us a transport out of here!"

3323, "(fr)Stay at your post, Cooper! Or I'll have you up for insubordination."

3324, "(fr)These people are fucking nuts."

3325, "(fr)Why don't we just evacuate the crew and be done with it? Leave the damned cargo."

3326, "(fr)Hoshikuzu, this is Euphonia way station. Hyperspace signature converging on your position. ETA ten seconds."

3327, "(fr)We've got company! It's a civilian ship."

3328, "(fr)What the hell are they doing? Crazy bastards."

3329, "(fr)This is the corvette Hoshikuzu to inbound civilian vessel. You are approaching a Sulsian security operation. State your intentions."

3330, "(fr)We are the Children of Renewal. The Lord created us to help those in need. We do the Lord's work by being here."

3331, "(fr)We have engineers and medical personnel on board dedicating their lives to serve. Let us help you, Compass Rose."

3332, "(fr)Oh hell. This is going to get interesting."

3333, "(fr)Renewal vessel, you have entered a live combat zone. We expect further hostile ships to arrive. We cannot guarantee your safety."

3334, "(fr)The Lord teaches us that important work is never easy. Everyone here knows the risks. We appreciate your concern."

3335, "(fr)You're a life saver, Outreach. Better than these useless Navy types. Get your engineers to fix my ship."

3336, "(fr)This is just great. Gunships, we now have two civilian vessels to keep alive."

3337, "(fr)God, that Shafer's a smug little bastard."

3338, "(fr)This is killing me. We're risking our lives for that piece of work."

3339, "(fr)Yeah, but we need the pay Meiks. Job's a job."

3340, "(fr)Hoshikuzu, Euphonia here. More signals inbound to your position. Coming in fast."

3341, "(fr)WARNING: HOSTILE ASM LAUNCH DETECTED"

3342, "(fr)Looks like this is it lad. Get ready."

3343, "(fr)This is the Equinox of the Malika People's Militia. You have violated our territory. Leave, or be destroyed."

3344, "(fr)Malikan ship, I will only warn you once. The penalty for interdicting merchant traffic is death. Break off immediately."

3345, "(fr)No matter. Our Javelins will turn that corporate frigate of yours to scrap. A warning to stay away from Malikan space."

3346, "(fr)Shit, they've got Javelins. This is going to get rough."

3347, "(fr)Lau here. She's getting torn up bad. We're losing power. "

3348, "(fr)Gunships, destroy the Equinox's missile launchers. We need to neutralise their artillery."

3349, "(fr)Ross, I'll distract the escorting fighters. You take care of that missile silo."

3350, "(fr)Good work lad. Let's head back."

