3995, "(fr)Corporate mercs. Overpaid, overpriced trash. Don't worry about them Ross, you and Meiks'll run rings around them. I'll bet they've never taken on a Combine battlegroup."

3996, "(fr)Hey. That's a Crown Navy ship."

3997, "(fr)Where?"

3998, "(fr)Up near that auxiliary ship. Just ahead of us."

3999, "(fr)That's an Arrowhead. One of the newest ship classes in the fleet. What's it doing here?"

4000, "(fr)Maybe they can help us...help us with Kendra and the refugees. You're both Commonwealth officers, would you be able to talk to them?"

4001, "(fr)I remember now...there was a report on CBN. Fleet wanted a ship at Covenant to monitor the situation. Just in case the refugee train decided to make its way to Commonwealth space."

4002, "(fr)They sent a warship to watch over a refugee convoy? Just in case they decided to seek asylum in Commonwealth space?"

4003, "(fr)I don't know the specifics Lau. Fleet doesn't tell me anything. I get my news from CBN."

4004, "(fr)Sulsian convoy, this is HMS Aria of the Crown Navy. What is the status of the Alban diplomatic personnel?"

4005, "(fr)This is Corazon Hayburn. Alban citizens are on board the main Renewal transport ship. I am in talks with the ship's master to facilitate our transfer to the Rondeau."

4006, "(fr)Acknowledged Ambassador. We await your confirmation. Please ensure all citizens have identification on hand at time of transfer."

4007, "(fr)Why are they only picking up Alban citizens? There's room for everyone on that auxiliary ship. They could save everyone."

4008, "(fr)Because they're Commonwealth citizens Lau. The Commonwealth doesn't have the resources to save everyone. Might as well ask that auxiliary ship to pick up every refugee in Covenant."

4009, "(fr)Don't worry Lau. The refugees will be ok."

4010, "(fr)Lau. There's been a development. Your cousin Kendra wants to speak to you."

4011, "(fr)What? Why? Get her on a secure channel, beam it to my comms."

4012, "(fr)What do you think that's all about?"

4013, "(fr)I've got a hunch it's related to that Combine admiral that attacked the refugee convoy. Kendra's got to be connected to her somehow."

4014, "(fr)That Kakotchka must have been pretty desperate. She was bloody damned close to crossing a big red line, attacking civilians like that."

4015, "(fr)Wouldn't surprise me if she was the same person who hired Kendra Lau to attack the Elgin and the other Commonwealth transports."

4016, "(fr)You think we're about to hear a confession from Kendra?"

4017, "(fr)Probably. There's a Commonwealth ship here ready to receive her. She's thinking she'll get off lightly if she spills her guts before we hand her over."

4018, "(fr)Interesting if it's true. Someone from ANI probably uncovered some big secret of Kakotchka's. No wonder she's panicking, locking down Sulsia."

4019, "(fr)If it turns out to be the Combine that's responsible for destroying Commonwealth transports, that's going to be taken as a declaration of war."

4020, "(fr)So you're saying the Commonwealth doesn't have the resources to  transport a few refugees? Your so-called $quoteGreat Power$quote?"

4021, "(fr)War's inevitable Meiks. Romanowska saw to that when she nuked Morik."

4022, "(fr)Sulsian fighters, this is Commander Cameron, HMS Aria. We have a situation that needs your cooperation."

4023, "(fr)This is Katherine Lau. We'll cooperate, but are currently employed by the Children of Renewal. You'll have to run it past them."

4024, "(fr)Reverend Frances on Covenant has nominated your wing specifically, Katherine Lau. "

4025, "(fr)Then I suppose we're at your service. What's the situation?"

4026, "(fr)Our sensors detected a heat spike on one of the freighters around Covenant. It may be a tritium leak from their fusion reactor but we need to confirm this and offer assistance if required."

4027, "(fr)If the ship has an unstable reactor, it could pose an explosive hazard to the surrounding ships in the convoy."

4028, "(fr)Have you tried contacting the freighter's master?"

4029, "(fr)Yes. All we're getting is an autogenerated message citing comms failure."

4030, "(fr)We're sending you the transponder of the freighter in question. We need an active scan of the cargo and the ship's comms subsystem to confirm her distress."

4031, "(fr)Ross, can you go? Meiks and I will stay with the Gogoltha in case we're needed."

4032, "(fr)Aria, Alfa 1 off Hopewell. Cargo painted. I see the tritium leak, but it's from the cargo box, not the ship's reactor."

4033, "(fr)Aria copies, Alfa 1. This is concerning. Scan the comms subsystem of the freighter."

4034, "(fr)Aria, Alfa 1. I've run a remote diagnostic on that freighter. Her transceiver is in full working condition."

4035, "(fr)Alfa 1, Aria Actual. Copy scan findings. This is concerning. The freighter may actually pose a threat to the convoy."

4036, "(fr)We've got movement! The freighter's burning towards the Sulsian refugee convoy!"

4037, "(fr)Commander! We've picked up antimatter catalysers inside that freighter's cargo manifest. Yields suggest planet-killer nuclear warheads."

4038, "(fr)This is Commander Anil Cameron of the HMS Aria to all ships in the vicinity. We have identified a radiological threat to Covenant and her attending ships. Make best speed to a distance of five klicks from the specified freighter."

4039, "(fr)WARNING: RADIOLOGICAL THREAT"

4040, "(fr)Oh shit!"

4041, "(fr)Shoot that freighter down Ross! They're suicide bombers on a mission to take out the Sulsian refugees."

4042, "(fr)Belay that lad! That's a planet cracker! It'll have at least a five kilometre radius. If that cargo container gets hit, it could detonate the warhead."

4043, "(fr)The freighter crew is going to detonate that warhead anyway! We have to take the chance!"

4044, "(fr)This is transport Remembering Gogoltha. We have two thousand souls aboard. Please help us!"

4045, "(fr)The warhead has gone active! Reading a sustained nuclear chain reaction on the freighter."

4046, "(fr)Lau, get yourself and Meiks clear of the blast radius! Every ship needs to scatter now! "

4047, "(fr)We're not leaving these refugees to die!"

4048, "(fr)Oh my god! It's heading straight for the Gogoltha."

4049, "(fr)Katherine Lau. The freighter is closing in on the Gogoltha. You've done all you can. Get your ships clear."

4050, "(fr)I'm...sorry Reverend. I'm sorry your people weren't able to see their Promised Land."

4051, "(fr)We wouldn't have got this far without you, Katherine. We may be lost, but Covenant and her people still need you. Bring them to salvation, in our memory."

4052, "(fr)God damn it."

4053, "(fr)We're not giving up now. Not after coming so far."

4054, "(fr)The Lord teaches us that the most important roads are often the most difficult. This is not a failure Katherine Lau. It is a test for our people, one that we will overcome."

4055, "(fr)Sulsian convoy. Be advised we may have identified a bypass for the warhead's detonation trigger. Continue to make distance from the freighter. Alfa 1, we need further assistance."

4056, "(fr)Say again Aria? Have you found a way to deactivate the warhead?"

4057, "(fr)Your scan helped pinpoint the freighter's transmitting frequencies to the nuclear warhead. We may be able to repurpose the warhead's receiver."

4058, "(fr)If you scan the rest of the freighter's subsystems, we'll be able to pin down exactly how the warhead's detonation trigger is linked to the freighter's systems and bypass them altogether."

4059, "(fr)That'll do it. Tactical, bypass the trigger for the warhead's arming sequence. It won't stop a contact detonation but it's a start."

4060, "(fr)Helm, maintain a tight formation to the freighter. That bypass is on a tightrope. If we lose signal integrity at any time, we're done for."

4061, "(fr)We've bought some time. Alfa 1, take out the freighter's engines. Be careful, try not to damage the cargo."

4062, "(fr)Reverend Lightowler, you can rest easier now. The freighter's dead in space and the warhead detonation trigger has been disabled."

4063, "(fr)You did it Ross!"

4064, "(fr)Great work lad. Now what do we do with it?"

4065, "(fr)Navo, prepare the Pollux Arrow for a boarding mission. We should apprehend the crew for questioning."

4066, "(fr)Yeah. Find out who's insane enough to nuke the Children of Renewal."

4067, "(fr)Solid copy Lau. There's a fire team on standby for deployment at short notice. I'll have them gear up."

4068, "(fr)WARNING: RADIOLOGICAL DETONATION"

4069, "(fr)We need to secure that freighter. Unfortunately  neither Aria nor Rondeau have any onboard marines."

