4846, "(fr)Walk with me Ross, McKearney. Murphy will debrief you on your performance, but I wanted to talk with you two first as the Longview's CO.

Admiral Colvin wanted me to pass her compliments on a job well done. The Osiris took heavy casualties but has made it to sanctuary at Ariel Station. We have started field repairs of most of the hull damage. With luck she'll be able to fight again soon.

We're left in a difficult position. The Osiris is the last survivor of Task Force 57 and the Federation has suffered defeats not only in Morik but along the entire front. Our position here has become a lot more precarious.

What happens next will be up to Admiral Colvin. I will be boarding the Osiris to formally transfer command of Fifth Fleet and debrief on events in Morik. The admiral has already ordered the transfer of all surviving Longview pilots and equipment to the carrier. What the admiral wants, the admiral gets.

It looks as though we're reaching the end of our efforts in Morik. I don't see what else we can achieve from here."

